## Local Machine Setup

1. System dependencies: Mac/Linux (preferably Ubuntu), Rails, Git, PostgreSQL (use <http://postgresapp.com/> for Mac, use package manager on Linux)
1. Open your terminal or command line
1. Install RVM (Ruby Version Manager) via <http://rvm.io/>
1. Install Ruby version 2.1.1: `rvm install 2.1.1`
1. Clone this project using Git
1. Install <%= app_name %> dependencies: `bundle`
1. Create local database: `rake db:create`
1. Migrate database: `rake db:migrate`
1. Seed database with default data: `rake db:seed`
1. Start server: `rails s`
1. Open browser at <http://localhost:3000>

## Deployment

1. Setup git remote pointing to Heroku server: `git remote add production <remote>`
1. Push to production remote: `git push production master`

